Posco Begins Construction of Steel Processing Plant in China

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-03-21T06:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/posco-begins-construction-of-steel-processing-plant-in-china.html
  Posco (005490) , the world’s third-biggest
steelmaker by output, began construction of an automotive steel
processing plant in  China  to meet demand from automakers in the
country.  The plant in Foshan, Gangdong province will process 450,000
metric tons of automotive steel a year when it is completed by
the end of 2012, the Pohang, South Korea-based company said in
an e-mailed statement today. The company didn’t disclose the
size of the investment.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Sangim Han at 
